21:24.450 --> 21:26.577
Hey, Moulin Rouge,

21:24.450 --> 21:26.577
what do you think?

21:26.619 --> 21:29.038
Jeweled elephant in one corner,

21:26.619 --> 21:29.038
Ewan McGregor in the other.

21:29.080 --> 21:30.706
Ooh, sounds yummy.

21:30.748 --> 21:32.708
[cellphone rings]

21:32.750 --> 21:34.752
What, Michel?

21:34.794 --> 21:38.131
I'm smelling something very

21:34.794 --> 21:38.131
funny coming from the kitchen.

21:38.172 --> 21:41.550
Could be a pungent cheese,

21:38.172 --> 21:41.550
could be arson.

21:41.592 --> 21:43.302
Should I call

21:41.592 --> 21:43.302
the firemen to come

21:43.343 --> 21:45.805
'or should I just fetch

21:43.343 --> 21:45.805
some crackers?'

21:49.016 --> 21:51.978
Ah, Rory. Good.

21:49.016 --> 21:51.978
I'm glad you're here.

21:52.019 --> 21:53.729
I wanted to talk to you

21:52.019 --> 21:53.729
about something.

21:53.771 --> 21:55.815
I think we need

21:53.771 --> 21:55.815
to discuss the incident

21:55.856 --> 21:57.024
at "The Daily News"

21:55.856 --> 21:57.024
the other day.

21:57.066 --> 21:58.442
What incident, Doyle?

21:58.484 --> 21:59.986
We were in the middle

21:58.484 --> 21:59.986
of a meeting.

22:00.027 --> 22:01.946
I, your editor,

22:00.027 --> 22:01.946
was talking.

22:01.988 --> 22:04.364
And suddenly, without warning,

22:01.988 --> 22:04.364
you flew out of the room.

22:04.406 --> 22:06.659
I was gone

22:04.406 --> 22:06.659
for five minutes, Doyle.

22:06.700 --> 22:08.368
Yes, but the very fact

22:06.700 --> 22:08.368
that you felt comfortable enough

22:08.410 --> 22:10.370
to leave

22:08.410 --> 22:10.370
signals a big problem.

22:10.412 --> 22:12.206
I had to talk to a friend.

22:12.248 --> 22:14.083
This is a matter

22:12.248 --> 22:14.083
of respect, Rory.

22:14.125 --> 22:16.460
Respect for the paper,

22:14.125 --> 22:16.460
respect for me.

22:16.502 --> 22:18.087
'Frankly, respect for yourself.'

22:18.129 --> 22:20.089
- Doyle--

22:18.129 --> 22:20.089
- I have a pebble in my shoe.

22:20.131 --> 22:21.924
Damn thing's been

22:20.131 --> 22:21.924
driving me crazy all day long.

22:23.759 --> 22:26.095
- 'Anyhow, where was I?'

22:23.759 --> 22:26.095
- My lack of respect for you.

22:26.137 --> 22:27.554
'Yes, good. Thank you.'

22:27.596 --> 22:29.015
You have to remember

22:27.596 --> 22:29.015
that this is college.

22:29.056 --> 22:30.516
You're training

22:29.056 --> 22:30.516
for real life here.

22:30.557 --> 22:31.934
You need to start

22:30.557 --> 22:31.934
developing boundaries

22:31.976 --> 22:33.560
between your work

22:31.976 --> 22:33.560
and your personal life.

22:33.602 --> 22:34.645
- Doyle!

22:33.602 --> 22:34.645
- What?

22:34.687 --> 22:35.771
Your sock is on my coffee table!

22:35.813 --> 22:36.856
Just for a second.

22:36.897 --> 22:38.524
You wanna talk about boundaries?

22:38.565 --> 22:41.277
You are here every day. You eat

22:38.565 --> 22:41.277
my food, you drink my soda.

22:41.319 --> 22:43.112
You have a key,

22:41.319 --> 22:43.112
and you don't even live here.

22:43.154 --> 22:44.655
Paris said

22:43.154 --> 22:44.655
<i>"Mi casa, su casa."</i>

22:44.697 --> 22:47.200
Great! Well, Paris'<i> casa</i>

22:44.697 --> 22:47.200
is right in there.

22:47.241 --> 22:49.451
So go in or get lost,

22:47.241 --> 22:49.451
because I have company coming

22:49.493 --> 22:51.287
and I don't want the first

22:49.493 --> 22:51.287
thing he sees when he walks in

22:51.329 --> 22:52.579
to be your feet or your face.

22:52.621 --> 22:54.414
But, but I'm your editor.

22:54.456 --> 22:57.210
Out! And take

22:54.456 --> 22:57.210
your pebble with you!

22:57.251 --> 22:58.502
I bet

22:57.251 --> 22:58.502
Woodward and Bernstein

22:58.544 --> 23:00.296
never tossed Ben Bradley

22:58.544 --> 23:00.296
out of their room!

23:00.338 --> 23:02.298
Ben Bradley

23:00.338 --> 23:02.298
kept his shoes on!

23:03.590 --> 23:05.467
I don't know

23:03.590 --> 23:05.467
